  <abstract>Enrique Reye and Niza Solari host. The entire episode discusses the horrible outbreak of cholera that happened in Peru. They discussed many of the issues regarding how the disease spread and some of the measures that were taken in order to contain the spread. When the death toll started forming the borders of Peru were closed in order to ensure that the disease stayed within the country. They discussed some of the support being sent to Peru and the work with organizations. They finished the episode with a traditional Chilean dance performed by the Chileno grupo Calafquen.</abstract>
